
{center}
{subhead} NewsCoaster{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

Announcing the release of NewsCoaster, a new shareware offline newsreader
for the Amiga. The unregistered version can be downloaded from Aminet, in
comm/news/newscoaster.lha
{p} {p}
Minimum Requirements:{p}
- 68020 or better{p}
- MUI{p}
- 4MB RAM (absolute minimum){p}
- OS3.0 or above
{p} {p}
Features:
{p} {p}
- Powerful control over which posts are downloaded (eg, set a maximum 
number of posts to download) - can configure for each newsgroup 
individually{p}
- Killfile on any header{p}
- Automatic killfile creation, based on a particular message (eg, kill
this thread, or kill all messages from this author){p}
- Choose not to download messages greater than a certain number of lines{p}
- Email support to reply to sender{p}
- Automatic rewrapping of text when replying - no more overspilling lines
{p} {p}
- Multithreaded interface - view messages whilst replying to others, and
having preferences windows open, continue to use the program whilst
uploading and downloading news{p}
- Import function which reads in all news items from a given directory
(and all sub-directories) allowing you to easily import news from your
old newsreader{p}
- MIME Version 1.0 for decoding files - can decode Quoted-Printable,
base64 and uuencoded messages{p}
- Attachments - base64 encoding{p}
- Search facilities - can search in a particular header, or in any
header, the message body, or the entire message{p}
- *, / and _ are converted to bolds, italics and underlines - but this
can be turned off (no more unreadable programming NGs that you get in some
newsreaders...){p}
- You can have eight signatures, with a default specified for each
newsgroup{p}
- Easy to use interface{p}
- AmigaGuide documentation{p}
- Download Group list option{p}
- Many more features..
{p} {p}
Please visit {link http://members.tripod.com/newscoaster}http://members.tripod.com/newscoaster{end} for more details.
{p} {p}
Thanks,
{p} {p}
Mark Harman